<dl id="n06055e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06055e">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06055e"> 55(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="green">[sp]</font>eak papa! doll</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Il n&apos;est pas douteux, d&apos;ailleurs, comme chacun de nous a pu l&apos;observer, que <mark>la poup&eacute;e</mark>, trop bien articul&eacute;e, <mark>qui disait m&ecirc;me <i>papa</i></mark>, <i>maman</i>, est, une fois le m&eacute;canisme d&eacute;rang&eacute;, plus int&eacute;ressante pour l&apos;enfant parce qu&apos;il s&apos;en sert &agrave; sa guise. <font color="green">[There is no doubt, moreover, as each of us was able to observe, that the doll, too well articulated, who said even dad, mom, is, once the mechanism disturbed, more interesting for the child because he uses it as he pleases.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 142</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
